Back by popular demand, the Ultimate Smile and Glam Giveaway 2021 is here!  This years lucky winner will receive:
• A custom smile by Doctor Kasiar
•An ultimate glam session from Brittany Aldean’s personal glam squad
•A professional photography session by the one and only Nanda Santos!  Follow the instructions below to enter!  

Don’t miss this opportunity of a lifetime!  Valued at over $60k!!

Here’s how to enter:
    1.   Like this post 👍
    2.  Send a 60 second video to Secondchancesmiles@thepracticetn.com telling us why you deserve to win the Ultimate Smile and Glam Giveaway 2021🌟 🦷
 3.   Include individual pictures of your smile 📸 

Contest begins NOW and runs through 8/16. The winner will be announced on 8/30 on my Instagram! Must be 18 years of age to enter. GOOD LUCK Y’ALL! XOXO

@nandaqsantos @cheriekilchriststyle @drmattkasiar @sweetmelissaxo @itsmadebybeck

node.text:
20 years have passed, yet each of us remember exactly where we were that morning. The heartache still remains. We still gasp in horror at the images of we’ve seen a million times. 
Never forget the sacrifices made and the lives that ended way too soon💔
The darkest of times were followed by the unity of this nation. May we all remember how blessed we are to be American and do all we can to protect this country🇺🇸

node.text: I can’t seem to shake the heartache💔 Bless our troops, the current ones and those who’ve paid the ultimate sacrifice to ensure we are all safe. We are forever grateful. Lord, please lift up their families🙌🏼🇺🇸

node.text: Remember the reason you are able to sleep peacefully at night. Remember the sacrifices made by the men and women in the military, and their families.  EVERY AMERICAN SHOULD BE ANGRY. THIS COULD HAVE BEEN PREVENTED. God bless them all🇺🇸💔🙏🏼

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Brittany Aldean on August 25, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text: I can’t believe I’m writing these words. Rheen, my buddy💔 What a ride we were on… traveling the world, joking every step of the way. I will love and miss you forever. Thank you for protecting us. You are family, forever and always. Our hearts are broken. I know you’re up in heaven with your Mama and Poncho 🐶 Lord knows they’ve missed you. Till we meet again my friend. Love you so much💔💔💔
